le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The job of an investment banker is to become a trust=
ed adviser to senior corporate executives, and then pitch those executives =
on doing deals (acquisitions, stock or bond=C2=A0offerings,=C2=A0etc.)=C2=
=A0that will generate fees for the investment bank. How does the banker dec=
ide what deals to pitch=3F Well, here is a non-exclusive list of things she=
 might consider:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40=
px; margin: 16px 0;"> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">She wants to preser=
ve her relationship with the client, so she will pitch deals that are=C2=A0=
<em>good for the client</em>. If she pitches some horrible derivative that =
will rip the client=E2=80=99s face off, she might get the business, but the=
 client will notice and she won=E2=80=99t get any=C2=A0<em>more=C2=A0</em>b=
usiness.</li> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">She wants to get paid, whic=
h means=C2=A0pitching deals that will make a lot of money for the bank. Doi=
ng an acquisition financed by leveraged loans is better than doing an open-=
market stock buyback, because it usually pays more.</li> <li style=3D"margi=
n-bottom: 5px;">She wants to get paid, which means pitching deals that gene=
rate revenue=C2=A0<em>for her=C2=A0</em>in the bank=E2=80=99s accounting. E=
xactly what that means will vary by bank, but in general the relationship b=
anker gets most of the credit for a merger advisory assignment and less of =
the credit for, say, pitching the company=E2=80=99s chief executive officer=
 on the bank=E2=80=99s wealth management capabilities. If the merger pitch =
succeeds, she=E2=80=99ll do the merger. If the wealth management pitch succ=
eeds, someone else =E2=80=94=C2=A0a wealth manager =E2=80=94=C2=A0will do t=
he work and get most of the credit.</li> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=
She wants to do fun cool deals and not bad boring deals. If she pitches a h=
igh-profile merger, and she ends up doing it, she will feel cool and have f=
un. If she pitches cash management services, she will be bored during the p=
itch, and will then never think about it again unless the client calls her =
with complaints.=C2=A0</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This whole mod=
